    <!-- Rules -->
    <Field Num="2" Kind="Put">
      <Geometry Up="1" Left="1" Low="19" Right="78"/>
      <Colors Foreground="cyan" Blink="False" Background="black"/>
      <Init Row="1" Col="2">This game presents several sticks aligned on four rows:</Init>
      <Init Row="2" Col="3">- seven sticks in the first row,</Init>
      <Init Row="3" Col="3">- five in the second,</Init>
      <Init Row="4" Col="3">- three in the third,</Init>
      <Init Row="5" Col="3">- and one in the fourth.</Init>

      <Init Row="7" Col="2">Each of us, at his turn, will remove some sticks, as many as we want,</Init>
      <Init Row="8" Col="3">with only two constraints:</Init>
      <Init Row="9" Col="4">- we must take at least one stick at each turn,</Init>
      <Init Row="10" Col="4">- at each turn, all the sticks we take must be on the same row.</Init>

      <Init Row="12" Col="2">I always play first at the beginning of a game, which gives you the</Init>
      <Init Row="13" Col="3">possibility to win each game.</Init>

      <Init Row="16" Col="2">Two variants are available:</Init>
      <Init Row="17" Col="3">- at Nim, the winner is the one who takes the last stick,</Init>
      <Init Row="18" Col="3">- at Marienbad, the player who takes the last stick loses.</Init>
    </Field>

